Preheat barbecue grill. Combine cilantro, olive oil, pepper sauce, garlic, and crushed red pepper in medium bowl. Cut beef steak into 1-1/4-inch pieces. Add beef to seasoning mixture; toss. Alternately thread beef and bell pepper onto six 10-inch metal skewers. Place kabobs on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. Grill, uncovered, about 8 to 11 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness, turning occasionally. Season with salt.